00:01.542 --> 00:02.375
(narrator)
Previously on "Hellcats  ...  "

00:02.375 --> 00:03.417
You sure school
is worth all this?

00:03.417 --> 00:06.333
Dan, I'm going to graduate,
pass the bar up North

00:06.333 --> 00:07.667
and work in the DA's office.

00:07.667 --> 00:08.959
You're applying
for a scholarship?

00:08.959 --> 00:09.959
I have one now,
for cheerleading.

00:09.959 --> 00:11.667
Cheerleading?
Whoa.

00:11.667 --> 00:13.333
(Savannah)
'Hello, Marti,
welcome to Cheertown.'

00:13.333 --> 00:15.333
I'm afraid
I let all of you down.

00:15.333 --> 00:17.667
I know now that
an innocent man went to jail

00:17.667 --> 00:20.000
for my crime and that's why
I've come forward

00:20.000 --> 00:21.500
and told the district attorney

00:21.500 --> 00:23.834
that Travis Guthrie must go free

00:23.834 --> 00:25.875
and I must do my time.

00:25.875 --> 00:27.875
- We'll be exclusive.
- 'You'd better not be joking.'

00:27.875 --> 00:30.792
'Dan and I were together. It was
a mistake. We were both drunk.'

00:30.792 --> 00:33.291
- Shut up!
- Do you know Dan Patch?

00:33.291 --> 00:35.625
He quit yesterday, cleaned out
his locker and said, "See ya."

00:35.625 --> 00:37.875
(Marti)
I lost Dan once,
I'm not losing him again.

00:37.875 --> 00:39.542
It's complicated,
but I'm in love

00:39.542 --> 00:41.166
with a guy who moved
without telling me

00:41.166 --> 00:42.375
and I'll probably
never see him again.

