♪ How the club vibratin' it's
enticin' let the beat knock ♪♪

01:51.750 --> 01:54.208
- Ah.
- Ha ha.

01:55.041 --> 01:56.291
Oh. Oh.

01:58.750 --> 02:00.125
[both laughing]

02:00.125 --> 02:01.458
Oh, Derrick.

02:01.458 --> 02:02.750
- Hey, coach.
- Hey.

02:02.750 --> 02:05.708
- Lookin' pretty good out there.
- Thanks.

02:05.708 --> 02:07.667
- Hey, can we talk?
- Sounds serious.

02:07.667 --> 02:11.125
- Ah, it kinda is.
- Okay.

02:11.125 --> 02:12.583
- Hey, Gretchen?
- 'Yeah?'

02:12.583 --> 02:14.625
- Give them a hard five, yeah?
- Will do.

02:14.625 --> 02:16.333
Guys, five minutes,
grab water, rest up.

02:16.333 --> 02:18.291
I've been deployed.

02:20.417 --> 02:22.792
- You're being deployed?
- Yeah.

02:22.792 --> 02:25.125
Yeah, my army reserve unit
got called up.

02:25.125 --> 02:27.625
We ship out in three days.

02:27.625 --> 02:29.792
How long you're gonna be
gone for?

02:29.792 --> 02:31.750
At least a year.

02:32.458 --> 02:33.625
[sighing]

02:33.625 --> 02:35.000
We start off in Germany.

02:35.000 --> 02:38.166
And from there, we could, um...

02:38.166 --> 02:40.333
We could be sent anywhere
they need doctors.

02:40.333 --> 02:42.125
Even the front lines?

02:42.125 --> 02:44.125
Well, these days we don't
really have front lines.

02:44.125 --> 02:46.458
Is that supposed
to make me feel better?

02:46.458 --> 02:49.375
Vanessa, it's in
everyone's best interest

02:49.375 --> 02:51.166
to keep the doctors safe.

02:51.166 --> 02:54.041
But, you know,
if something should happen--

02:54.041 --> 02:55.500
Don't talk like that.

02:55.500 --> 02:57.792
I want to make sure
you're taken care of.

02:57.792 --> 03:00.375
I think that we should
step up the timetable.

03:00.375 --> 03:03.000
Let's get married
before I ship out.

03:03.000 --> 03:04.417
Oh. Uh...

03:04.417 --> 03:07.834
- Um...wow.
- We'll do it legally now.

03:07.834 --> 03:09.834
You know, with the Justice
of the Peace and then we'll have

03:09.834 --> 03:11.625
a big celebration
when I get back.

03:11.625 --> 03:13.417
Okay, but I-I don't care
about the benefits, you know?

03:13.417 --> 03:16.208
It's not just about
the benefits, Vanessa.

03:16.208 --> 03:18.375
If I have to go,
I want to know that I'm married

03:18.375 --> 03:21.000
to the woman that I love.

03:21.000 --> 03:24.625
I just...I just don't
wanna have any regrets.

03:28.000 --> 03:29.750
Okay.

03:29.750 --> 03:32.333
Let's do it, then.

03:32.333 --> 03:35.083
[both laughing]

03:35.083 --> 03:37.875
[instrumental music]

03:41.125 --> 03:42.667
How's Travis working out?

03:42.667 --> 03:44.041
Best server I got.

03:44.041 --> 03:45.917
Good roommate, too.

03:45.917 --> 03:47.708
Doesn't leave his hair
in the drain

03:47.708 --> 03:50.000
like other people I could name.

03:50.000 --> 03:51.917
Do you really want to start
listing annoying habits?

03:51.917 --> 03:54.333
- Well, if we did, I'd win.
- You wish.

03:54.333 --> 03:56.166
[chuckling]

03:56.166 --> 03:57.542
I appreciate you helping him.

03:57.542 --> 04:00.041
Oh, honey, it's my pleasure.

04:00.041 --> 04:02.208
The good news is
I have come up with a way

04:02.208 --> 04:04.083
for you to pay me back.

04:04.083 --> 04:07.542
That does sound like good news.
What is it?

04:07.542 --> 04:11.083
Well, first of all, wipe that
suspicious look off your face.

04:11.083 --> 04:12.583
It's more than
a little insulting.

04:12.583 --> 04:14.417
Oh, so insulting
you're dodging the question?

04:14.417 --> 04:17.083
Well, I might
not even ask you now.

04:17.083 --> 04:20.041
Oh, good. Thanks for lunch.

04:21.791 --> 04:25.792
I need you to sing on Saturday
at an event I planned.

04:25.792 --> 04:28.625
Is this event by any chance
Jimmy Patch's wedding?

04:28.625 --> 04:32.083
Well, what difference does it
make? You'd be doing me a favor.

04:32.083 --> 04:34.917
Look at Travis.

04:34.917 --> 04:36.959
How happy is he?

04:36.959 --> 04:39.917
No way. No. Dan's gonna be
there, he's the best man.

04:39.917 --> 04:44.583
That's right, and he's only
in town for the weekend.

04:44.583 --> 04:46.583
You know for a fact
he's leaving?

04:46.583 --> 04:48.875
Look at you. You are interested.

04:48.875 --> 04:51.917
And this might be
your only chance to see him.

04:51.917 --> 04:55.959
No. Save the mind games, mom.
I'm not, I'm not doin' it.

04:55.959 --> 04:59.583
You know, Dan's daddy
asked for you specially.

04:59.583 --> 05:03.708
It would really break his heart
if you don't do this.

05:05.125 --> 05:08.083
Well, you can ask him yourself.

05:08.083 --> 05:09.750
What? You didn't.

05:12.458 --> 05:15.166
- Marti Beth.
- Hey, Mr. Patch.

05:17.250 --> 05:20.458
A little bird tells me you're
having about a stage fright.

05:20.458 --> 05:23.083
Oh. Stage fright?

05:23.083 --> 05:24.917
Honey, I had to tell him that.

05:24.917 --> 05:26.917
[chuckling]
I understand.

05:26.917 --> 05:29.125
I get it myself
at school board meetings

05:29.125 --> 05:32.000
but I'm here to say that you
have nothing to be afraid of.

05:32.000 --> 05:34.000
You are among family.

05:34.000 --> 05:37.458
Hell, I've known you
since you were about that tall.

05:37.458 --> 05:40.000
Mildred loved
your singing voice.

05:40.000 --> 05:43.166
Made her so happy when you'd
come on over and play piano.

05:43.166 --> 05:45.500
We never could afford
one of our own.

05:45.500 --> 05:47.333
What do you say, Marti?

05:47.333 --> 05:48.959
Give it a try?

05:51.667 --> 05:53.834
It would be my pleasure.

05:53.834 --> 05:56.542
- Attagirl.
- Yeah, you got it.

05:59.000 --> 06:00.083
[sighing]

06:02.041 --> 06:03.917
(Savannah)
'So he's leaving right
after the wedding?'

06:03.917 --> 06:07.500
That's what his dad told my mom.

06:07.500 --> 06:09.875
Look, I'm not jumping at the
prospect of awkward small talk

06:09.875 --> 06:13.500
with a guy who hates me, okay?

06:13.500 --> 06:16.083
I don't think the problem
is that he hates you.

06:19.250 --> 06:22.208
If you want me to,
I'll back out.

06:22.208 --> 06:25.750
I'm not gonna let anything
mess up our friendship again.

06:26.834 --> 06:28.625
Then be honest with me.

06:30.041 --> 06:32.333
Do you still have feelings
for Dan?

06:33.208 --> 06:35.166
Romantic feelings?

06:36.542 --> 06:39.417
[instrumental music]

06:40.708 --> 06:42.750
No.

06:42.750 --> 06:45.250
'I mean, it's confusing, uh...'

06:45.250 --> 06:49.041
I didn't before he left,
and then...while he was gone

06:49.041 --> 06:51.875
I really missed him a lot
more than I thought I would.

06:52.875 --> 06:55.417
So I don't know.

06:56.542 --> 06:57.875
'Maybe that means something.'

06:59.583 --> 07:01.375
How about you?

07:03.750 --> 07:07.708
In spite of everything
that's happened...

07:07.708 --> 07:09.583
...yeah.

07:09.583 --> 07:12.083
And I just wish
I could tell him.

07:12.083 --> 07:14.250
Well, you should then, right?

07:14.250 --> 07:16.041
I think the only way for us
to settle this

07:16.041 --> 07:19.083
once and for all is
if we both go to the wedding.

07:19.083 --> 07:20.875
Wait, settle this?
What are we settling?

07:20.875 --> 07:23.583
Level playing field.
All above board.

07:23.583 --> 07:25.250
We both go to the wedding,
put our best feet forward

07:25.250 --> 07:26.875
and see what happens with Dan.

07:26.875 --> 07:28.583
[giggling]

07:28.583 --> 07:30.125
You know, for a second there
I thought you were actually

07:30.125 --> 07:32.708
suggesting some kind of
competition for Dan.

07:32.708 --> 07:34.917
Which of course, you can't be,
because that would be crazy.

07:34.917 --> 07:36.208
[chuckling]

07:36.208 --> 07:38.083
It's not a competition.

07:38.083 --> 07:40.125
It's...

07:40.125 --> 07:41.625
...an emotional exploratory.

07:41.625 --> 07:43.458
- What?
- Yeah, we both show up.

07:43.458 --> 07:46.125
He sees us, he talks to us

07:46.125 --> 07:48.792
and what's meant to be
is meant to be.

07:48.792 --> 07:51.458
I just don't have an invitation
to the wedding, though.

07:51.458 --> 07:53.792
Do you think your mom could
hire me as a cater waiter?

07:53.792 --> 07:56.917
This is not a cheer competition,
Savannah.

07:58.834 --> 08:01.083
I have to see him.

08:01.083 --> 08:02.417
Please.

08:05.125 --> 08:09.041
- Okay. Fine.
- Thank you.

08:11.125 --> 08:13.083
But it's not a competition,
okay?

08:13.083 --> 08:14.708
Of course not.

08:17.834 --> 08:20.792
[instrumental music]

08:22.625 --> 08:24.000
Hey, Audrey?

08:24.000 --> 08:25.875
Hey, this is Savannah Monroe.

08:25.875 --> 08:28.542
Do you think that she could
get me in for highlights today?

08:31.166 --> 08:32.166
(Lewis)
'Ahem.'

08:32.166 --> 08:33.667
Hey! Damian.

08:33.667 --> 08:35.125
Hey, now, knock yourself out,
man, I'm done.

08:35.125 --> 08:37.457
Oh, thanks. I need
to get my strength up.

08:37.457 --> 08:38.833
Rough practice?

08:38.833 --> 08:40.707
- I went and saw Jake today.
- 'Ooh.'

08:40.707 --> 08:42.707
- Talk about depressing.
- Oh, hm.

08:42.707 --> 08:46.417
Jail makes the dorm rooms
look like Peabody hotel.

08:48.166 --> 08:51.000
- I thought you hated Jake.
- I feel bad for the guy.

08:51.000 --> 08:53.333
Coach has us taking turns.
I went last week.

08:53.333 --> 08:55.667
(Damian)
'I mean, Jake and I,
we've obviously had our issues'

08:55.667 --> 08:58.041
but circumstances change,
relationships change.

08:58.041 --> 09:00.166
I mean, take us for instance.

09:00.166 --> 09:01.959
Who would've thought
we'd have ever ended up friends?

09:01.959 --> 09:04.875
We only became friends
after you were properly punished

09:04.875 --> 09:08.333
for circulating my private
photos all around campus.

09:08.333 --> 09:10.083
I bet Jake wishes
he had those photos right now.

09:10.083 --> 09:12.208
[chuckling]

09:12.208 --> 09:14.083
He says hello, by the way.

09:14.083 --> 09:16.583
And he misses you.

09:16.583 --> 09:19.667
And he wonders why
you haven't come to visit him.

09:19.667 --> 09:22.667
We're through. I...

09:22.667 --> 09:24.708
I don't want to give him
any false hope.

09:24.708 --> 09:27.542
(Damian)
'Hey, I'm just
relaying the message.'

09:27.542 --> 09:29.542
'Well, I should
get to practice.'

09:29.542 --> 09:31.917
Work off your fries. See ya.

09:33.250 --> 09:35.375
He said
you promised to visit him.

09:35.375 --> 09:38.208
- Is that true?
- Sort of.

09:39.834 --> 09:41.208
Yeah.

09:41.208 --> 09:42.834
Look, Jake messed up, alright

09:42.834 --> 09:44.542
but in the end,
he did the right thing.

09:44.542 --> 09:46.625
I practically had to swindle him
to get him there.

09:46.625 --> 09:48.875
I am not shedding any tears
over Jake Harrow.

09:48.875 --> 09:51.125
And I'm certainly
not going to visit him.

09:51.125 --> 09:53.917
Okay, is there somethin' else
going on here?

09:55.417 --> 09:56.959
This conversation's over.

09:58.625 --> 10:01.583
So I thought we'd put
the wedding party table here

10:01.583 --> 10:04.250
with the little arrangements
facing the stage

10:04.250 --> 10:05.834
and the dance floor.

10:05.834 --> 10:07.875
W-where's the baby's breath?
I don't see baby's breath.

10:07.875 --> 10:09.750
Oh, the baby's breath's
right over here.

10:09.750 --> 10:11.375
Here it is.

10:11.375 --> 10:12.959
It's...white.

10:12.959 --> 10:15.708
- I-it's white!
- Yes.

10:15.708 --> 10:17.542
- Baby's breath is white.
- It is?

10:17.542 --> 10:20.917
I didn't know that. I...
What are we gonna do?

10:20.917 --> 10:23.959
It's all over my wedding
reception looking...white.

10:23.959 --> 10:26.291
Just-just try and relax.

10:26.291 --> 10:29.291
She's a little stressed out
with all her relatives in town.

10:29.291 --> 10:30.959
My mother hates white flowers.

10:30.959 --> 10:34.125
I mean, my father sent her
white roses the entire time

10:34.125 --> 10:36.792
he was having an affair
with his business partner.

10:36.792 --> 10:38.542
This is a nightmare.

10:38.542 --> 10:40.250
- I will call the florist.
- Thank you.

10:40.250 --> 10:41.625
- Mm-hmm.
- Thank you so much.

10:41.625 --> 10:43.875
- Mm-hmm.
- Hey.

10:45.166 --> 10:46.792
[sighing]

10:46.792 --> 10:48.750
I appreciate your patience.

10:48.750 --> 10:50.583
So how's everything coming
with the entertainment?

10:50.583 --> 10:52.917
Good, we have
locked down Faber Drive

10:52.917 --> 10:55.458
and Marti has agreed to sing
some Rolling Stones.

10:55.458 --> 10:58.458
Awesome. Uh, Theresa and I
met at a Stones concert.

10:58.458 --> 11:00.458
- They're our band.
- Oh.

11:00.458 --> 11:02.834
Hey, I, I hate to listen in
without permission

11:02.834 --> 11:05.333
but d-did you say
Marti's singin' at the wedding?

11:05.333 --> 11:07.125
- Uh-huh.
- Oh, my God.

11:07.125 --> 11:09.500
What's wrong with Marti? Did
something happen to her voice?

11:09.500 --> 11:11.166
- No. Nothing's wrong.
- No. Everything's fine.

11:11.166 --> 11:12.667
- Right, Dan?
- Marti's great. Yeah.

11:12.667 --> 11:15.458
Okay, we're gonna get
some fresh air.

11:15.458 --> 11:16.667
Bye.

11:18.625 --> 11:23.125
Yeah ,Jimmy always had a soft
spot for high-maintenance girls.

11:27.000 --> 11:28.625
Oh!

11:28.625 --> 11:30.000
What's in this?

11:30.000 --> 11:31.959
Oh, star fruit.

11:31.959 --> 11:33.500
A little bit of vodka.

11:33.500 --> 11:35.000
Yeah?

11:35.000 --> 11:37.834
So, um...

11:37.834 --> 11:40.708
...how long has it been
since you've seen Marti?

11:40.708 --> 11:43.792
Did-did you know that she got
that man, Travis, out of prison?

11:43.792 --> 11:45.208
Mm-hmm.

11:45.208 --> 11:47.208
And she's doing something
different with her hair.

11:47.208 --> 11:48.500
- Ha ha.
- Uh-uh.

11:48.500 --> 11:51.041
- Wanda, don't do this.
- Oh.

11:51.041 --> 11:53.166
What are you talkin' about?
Do what?

11:53.166 --> 11:55.542
No, I let you mess
with my head once.

11:55.542 --> 11:57.375
I ended up
in a world of confusion

11:57.375 --> 12:00.583
I've just recently found
my way out of, so, no.

12:00.583 --> 12:03.000
My relationship with Marti
is off-limits to you.

12:03.000 --> 12:05.166
Ugh, fine.

12:06.667 --> 12:08.375
Is she okay?

12:08.375 --> 12:10.417
She's good...

12:10.417 --> 12:13.041
...but she misses you.

12:13.041 --> 12:15.291
- How about Savannah?
- Savannah?

12:15.291 --> 12:17.083
Yeah, I, uh...

12:17.083 --> 12:18.625
I hurt Savannah real bad.

12:18.625 --> 12:22.250
Oh, well, she seems fine to me.

12:22.250 --> 12:24.875
Alright.

12:24.875 --> 12:27.875
Well, I'm gonna go make sure
everything's okay with Theresa.

12:27.875 --> 12:30.708
I'll see you later
at the wedding.

12:30.708 --> 12:32.250
Savannah.

12:32.250 --> 12:35.166
[blues music]

12:39.834 --> 12:41.333
You okay?

12:42.917 --> 12:44.792
I'm getting married.

12:44.792 --> 12:47.458
- I know that.
- Hm. Tomorrow.

12:49.917 --> 12:52.041
Tomorrow?

12:52.041 --> 12:53.750
Oh.

12:53.750 --> 12:57.166
So we're just gonna bite
the bullet and just do it.

12:57.166 --> 12:59.291
Alright, I guess
that doesn't leave much time

12:59.291 --> 13:01.542
to throw
your bachelorette party, then?

13:01.542 --> 13:02.959
I guess not.

13:04.417 --> 13:06.750
- I know what you're thinking.
- Do you?

13:06.750 --> 13:09.583
Yeah, I'm not doing this
out of guilt or obligation.

13:09.583 --> 13:12.792
I am marrying Derrick
because we are good together.

13:12.792 --> 13:14.458
Given a lot of time
in this relationship

13:14.458 --> 13:16.417
and I'm not throwing it all away

13:16.417 --> 13:18.959
just because
we have to rush it a bit.

13:18.959 --> 13:21.000
Hm, I noticed you didn't list

13:21.000 --> 13:22.917
"I love him"
as one of your reasons.

13:22.917 --> 13:26.125
Oh, guess that goes
without saying, I love him.

13:26.125 --> 13:27.792
We've worked very hard
on this relationship

13:27.792 --> 13:30.667
and I'm not throwing it all away
on a whim.

13:30.667 --> 13:32.750
- What whim?
- You.

13:32.750 --> 13:34.291
You're the whim.

13:34.291 --> 13:35.625
Bad whim.

13:35.625 --> 13:37.083
Alright, let me ask you this.

13:37.083 --> 13:38.792
What if the roles were reversed?

13:38.792 --> 13:40.333
Would you want
Derrick to marry you

13:40.333 --> 13:41.750
if he felt about
another woman the way

13:41.750 --> 13:44.417
that...I think
that you feel about me?

13:44.417 --> 13:47.250
[scoffing]
Don't flatter yourself.

13:47.250 --> 13:49.417
And I'm leaving.

13:49.417 --> 13:51.125
Y-you don't think
he can sense it, though

13:51.125 --> 13:53.125
'I mean, that you're wavering?'

13:53.125 --> 13:54.333
Of course,
he wants to put a ring

13:54.333 --> 13:55.667
on your finger before he goes.

13:55.667 --> 13:58.000
- He's scared.
- Scared of what?

13:58.000 --> 14:00.000
He's scared that you're not
gonna be here when he gets back.

14:00.000 --> 14:02.834
Okay, I think I'll get
my relationship advice

14:02.834 --> 14:05.333
from someone else,
'cause you, my friend

14:05.333 --> 14:08.834
are not to be trusted
with this particular subject.

14:08.834 --> 14:10.834
Well, I suppose not

14:10.834 --> 14:13.083
but even a stop clock
is right twice a day.

14:13.083 --> 14:14.625
Goodbye, Red.

14:14.625 --> 14:16.500
Hey, are you guys
registered anywhere?

14:16.500 --> 14:17.917
