19:23.834 --> 19:26.083
♪ Oh m-y ♪♪

19:26.083 --> 19:27.583
[all applauding]

19:29.166 --> 19:32.041
[instrumental music]

19:37.500 --> 19:41.500
You know how to sell a song,
Marti Perkins.

19:41.500 --> 19:43.750
Hey, you know,
wedding audiences are easy.

19:43.750 --> 19:46.041
- Lots of booze and optimism.
- Yeah.

19:47.708 --> 19:51.667
So your mom's done
a spectacular job.

19:51.667 --> 19:54.875
I think she's even
charmed my daddy, too.

19:54.875 --> 19:57.291
Oh, watch out, you might end up
with a new stepmom.

19:57.291 --> 20:00.708
Which, I guess, would make
you and me brother and sister.

20:00.708 --> 20:03.166
Not since Luke and Leia, huh?

20:07.500 --> 20:10.041
- Okay.
- Yo, M, uh, wait up.

20:10.041 --> 20:12.417
- Yeah.
- We need to talk.

20:14.834 --> 20:16.917
I owe you an apology.

20:16.917 --> 20:19.542
- No, you don't.
- Yeah, I do.

20:19.542 --> 20:21.834
I left you
with a big mess in your lap

20:21.834 --> 20:23.208
and then I wouldn't take
your calls and I--

20:23.208 --> 20:26.917
Okay, stop.
You don't owe me an apology.

20:26.917 --> 20:30.708
I was horrible
about how I handled everything.

20:30.708 --> 20:33.041
- I've thought a lot about--
- I've been thinking...

20:33.041 --> 20:34.834
Sorry. You first.

20:34.834 --> 20:36.333
Ladies first.

20:38.000 --> 20:39.542
Okay, well, um...

20:41.500 --> 20:44.458
It's been really weird
around here without you.

20:44.458 --> 20:47.667
- And I've been thinking--
- Mushroom puff?

20:47.667 --> 20:49.875
Savannah.

20:49.875 --> 20:51.375
You look good.

20:51.375 --> 20:53.917
Thank you.

20:53.917 --> 20:56.375
I hope
I didn't interrupt anything.

20:56.375 --> 20:58.041
- No.
- No. No, not at all.

20:58.041 --> 21:00.750
- I'm glad to see you.
- 'Dan!'

21:00.750 --> 21:04.917
- There you are.
- Hey, you.

21:04.917 --> 21:08.083
Um, Marti, Savannah,
this is Vicky.

21:08.083 --> 21:10.250
She came up to Memphis with me
from New Orleans.

21:10.250 --> 21:14.083
We, uh, met on a boat
doing oil-spill reclamation.

21:14.083 --> 21:16.750
I'm passionate about shorebirds.

21:16.750 --> 21:20.834
I've cleaned oil
off of 276 of them so far.

21:22.458 --> 21:24.750
[sighing]
Are those mushroom puffs?

21:24.750 --> 21:26.458
Awesome.

21:35.959 --> 21:37.208
[guitar music]

21:38.792 --> 21:42.250
The chicks live in the marsh
where the oil is

21:42.250 --> 21:44.834
and then the oil gets on
their little downy bellies

21:44.834 --> 21:49.125
and then they clean their
feathers and, well, you see that

21:49.125 --> 21:53.625
276 times, it's devastating.

21:53.625 --> 21:55.583
Devastating.

21:55.583 --> 21:58.792
I admire your dedication.

21:58.792 --> 22:02.291
I can't imagine how those birds
get along without you.

22:02.291 --> 22:04.166
You should go back.

22:05.458 --> 22:07.500
Uh, I think I need to sit down.

22:07.500 --> 22:09.959
Yeah, okay. Excuse us.

22:12.166 --> 22:13.291
[scoffing]

22:13.291 --> 22:16.834
"It's devastating. Devastating."

22:16.834 --> 22:19.834
I mean, uh, I don't get it.
What does Dan see in her?

22:19.834 --> 22:23.625
Her flawless, protruding
breasts? I don't know.

22:23.625 --> 22:25.542
I want to punch him.

22:25.542 --> 22:29.000
Hey, I, uh, appreciate the save.

22:29.000 --> 22:30.291
What save?

22:30.291 --> 22:32.000
If you hadn't come up
when you did

22:32.000 --> 22:34.667
I would've made a complete
fool of myself with Dan. Huh.

22:34.667 --> 22:36.792
You were going to tell him
how you really feel?

22:36.792 --> 22:40.542
That you wanted to be
more than friends?

22:40.542 --> 22:42.875
- I-I don't know.
- You don't know?

22:42.875 --> 22:44.959
I have no idea what was going
to come out of my mouth.

22:44.959 --> 22:46.959
I-I do miss, Dan.

22:46.959 --> 22:48.458
And then there's
this stupid competition

22:48.458 --> 22:50.708
we're not having.

22:50.708 --> 22:52.834
Whatever I said would've been
a complete disaster

22:52.834 --> 22:55.625
and I'm lucky you stopped me.

22:55.625 --> 22:58.500
That was really honest.

22:58.500 --> 23:00.166
Thank you.

23:05.083 --> 23:07.208
Dan and I work as friends.

23:07.208 --> 23:08.708
'That's what I want.'

23:08.708 --> 23:10.917
That's all I want.

23:12.917 --> 23:15.417
And I'm sorry
he's with someone else.

23:15.417 --> 23:19.041
I wish he were with you,
making you happy.

23:19.041 --> 23:21.083
Don't count me out yet.

23:21.083 --> 23:23.375
Come on, he's with someone.

23:23.375 --> 23:24.708
For now.

23:24.708 --> 23:25.875
Now, if you'll excuse me

23:25.875 --> 23:28.291
I have to pass out the nibbles.

23:34.708 --> 23:37.250
♪ Tonight candle light... ♪

23:37.250 --> 23:39.041
Hey, see that girl over there

23:39.041 --> 23:41.667
in the blue dress?

23:41.667 --> 23:43.708
You want to make a quick 40?

23:43.708 --> 23:46.250
- No, make that 50.
- Um, sure.

23:46.250 --> 23:49.083
Just get her talking
about shorebirds, okay?

23:49.083 --> 23:50.250
Okay.

23:51.917 --> 23:55.208
♪ What if there's no goodbye ♪♪

23:55.208 --> 23:58.083
What are you wearing?

23:58.083 --> 24:00.750
I spilled on my uniform. Yeah.

24:00.750 --> 24:03.750
Yeah, lucky for me,
I had this dress in my car.

24:03.750 --> 24:06.417
Just think of me
as a stealth waiter.

24:06.417 --> 24:08.375
- Come back here.
- Sorry, Wanda.

24:08.375 --> 24:11.291
Those guests
are looking really thirsty.

24:11.291 --> 24:13.708
Wanda? We need to fix the cake.

24:13.708 --> 24:16.417
My mother's new boyfriend
is allergic to dairy.

24:16.417 --> 24:19.417
It's buttercream icing.
You know, let's get you a drink.

24:19.417 --> 24:22.750
Have you ever had
a mood-stabilizer martini?

24:22.750 --> 24:24.583
- No.
- 'Oh, they're great.'

24:24.583 --> 24:27.417
Come on. Give me
something with everything.

24:27.417 --> 24:31.291
We moved the bird
to a second clean pan.

24:31.291 --> 24:34.458
Now, there we have
this special spa nozzle

24:34.458 --> 24:36.667
that propels the water
at sufficient pressure.

24:36.667 --> 24:38.250
Uh, cheers.

24:38.250 --> 24:39.959
Hey, Dan.

24:39.959 --> 24:41.458
Mr. Patch,
it's good to see you again.

24:41.458 --> 24:44.083
The pleasure's mine.
And call me James.

24:44.083 --> 24:45.458
Yes.

24:45.458 --> 24:47.667
Uh, Savannah,
these are my cousins--

24:47.667 --> 24:49.417
Michael, Chris and Frank.

24:49.417 --> 24:51.792
'And Michael's wife, Casey,
Chris' girlfriend, Jill'

24:51.792 --> 24:53.166
'and Frank's wife, Kimmie.'

24:53.166 --> 24:54.834
Incidentally,
congratulations, Kimmie.

24:54.834 --> 24:57.166
It's impossible to tell
you had a baby six months ago.

24:57.166 --> 25:00.792
- Uh, thank you.
- Oh, you're good.

25:00.792 --> 25:04.834
[chuckling]
Yeah, uh, Dan would pull out
a photo album from time to time

25:04.834 --> 25:06.750
'and I have a good memory
for faces.'

25:09.333 --> 25:11.250
(James)
'So anyway, uh...'

25:12.625 --> 25:14.000
Whoosh!

25:14.000 --> 25:15.041
Dry.

25:15.041 --> 25:17.625
It's very impressive.

25:17.625 --> 25:19.875
Now, we don't normally condone
the use of leg bands--

25:19.875 --> 25:21.041
- Okay.
- But in some--

25:21.041 --> 25:22.375
This isn't worth it.

25:22.375 --> 25:24.375
She can keep her 50 bucks.

25:24.375 --> 25:27.792
We never expected Mikey
to ever get married.

25:30.875 --> 25:32.667
Uh, Dan, could we go outside?

25:32.667 --> 25:34.500
I just need to talk to you.

25:34.500 --> 25:36.208
Dan?

25:36.208 --> 25:37.708
Who is this person?

25:37.708 --> 25:39.333
Oh, you-you met her
a little while ago.

25:39.333 --> 25:41.792
No, I mean, who is she to you?

25:41.792 --> 25:44.208
She just paid some guy
$50 to ask me questions

25:44.208 --> 25:47.000
'about the shorebird
rescue project.'

25:47.875 --> 25:50.000
Do you deny it?

25:54.667 --> 25:56.875
I think it's time
to cut the cake.

25:56.875 --> 25:58.875
Except for those
who are lactose intolerant.

25:58.875 --> 26:01.708
Yes, dear. Uh, Savannah,
we are running low on plates.

26:01.708 --> 26:03.375
Be a darling and go grab some.

26:03.375 --> 26:05.208
Alright, come on.
Let's go. Come on.

26:05.208 --> 26:08.625
I would like to know
what the hell's going on here.

26:08.625 --> 26:11.208
- 'Come on, everybody.'
- Uh-uh.

26:11.208 --> 26:13.250
I'm assuming
you didn't invite Savannah?

26:13.250 --> 26:15.708
No. No, I have no idea
why she's here.

26:15.708 --> 26:17.583
No idea? Really?

26:17.583 --> 26:20.417
I thought you were the smart one
in the family.

26:20.417 --> 26:25.041
Figure she wants to talk to me,
make me explain myself.

26:25.041 --> 26:27.917
It's a conversation
I'm not anxious to have.

26:27.917 --> 26:31.583
- Hurt her pretty bad, huh?
- Yeah.

26:31.583 --> 26:34.375
So you brought the bird woman
of Lake Pontchartrain along

26:34.375 --> 26:37.250
as what, a human shield?

26:37.250 --> 26:40.917
I thought having a date along
would keep my head straight

26:40.917 --> 26:43.208
keep me from doing
something stupid.

26:43.208 --> 26:45.458
Any of this
got something to do with Marti?

26:45.458 --> 26:46.583
How?

26:46.583 --> 26:48.250
She didn't wanna show up today.

26:48.250 --> 26:50.083
Wanda came to me
with some cock-and-bull story

26:50.083 --> 26:51.250
about stage fright.

26:51.250 --> 26:53.959
Stage fright? Marti? Come on.

26:53.959 --> 26:56.291
- I played along.
- Yeah.

26:58.250 --> 27:01.750
Yeah, things got a little weird
between us before I left.

27:01.750 --> 27:03.583
Broke up with Savannah
because of it.

27:03.583 --> 27:05.959
Marti.

27:05.959 --> 27:08.417
- My, my.
- What?

27:08.417 --> 27:11.458
I love that girl as a daughter,
but she is a bad fit for you.

27:11.458 --> 27:14.125
- Why?
- She's a train wreck.

27:14.125 --> 27:17.750
- You're a train wreck.
- Thank you, dad.

27:17.750 --> 27:19.792
I say that with love.

27:19.792 --> 27:21.417
I mean, two train wrecks
are exciting to watch

27:21.417 --> 27:23.458
but people get hurt.

27:23.458 --> 27:25.125
You need a girl like your mom

27:25.125 --> 27:28.291
somebody to call you
on your crap.

27:28.291 --> 27:30.458
You know how I knew
your mother was the one?

27:30.458 --> 27:32.458
She made me try harder.

27:32.458 --> 27:34.291
She made me
want to be a better person

27:34.291 --> 27:36.583
and believe that I could be.

27:36.583 --> 27:39.083
When you were seeing Savannah,
I saw a little of that

27:39.083 --> 27:41.291
saw you behaving
like a grown-up.

27:41.291 --> 27:43.166
It's a good color on you,
my son.

27:43.166 --> 27:44.667
If you're trying
to make me feel worse

27:44.667 --> 27:47.458
about screwing up
with her...it's working.

27:47.458 --> 27:50.333
Good. Then my fatherly work here
is done.

27:50.333 --> 27:52.125
Oh, and, uh, ahem, are you aware

27:52.125 --> 27:56.125
that Vicky, uh,
cleaned up 276 shorebirds?

27:56.125 --> 27:58.750
Yeah, that may have come up
once or twice.

28:01.959 --> 28:03.458
[sighing]

28:06.125 --> 28:07.792
[chuckling]
You're still not dressed?

28:07.792 --> 28:12.333
Uh, neither one of these
feels quite...right.

28:12.333 --> 28:15.000
Honey, you're gonna
look gorgeous in either one.

28:15.000 --> 28:17.000
Hm.

28:17.000 --> 28:19.166
Okay, so I printed out
the, uh, online form

28:19.166 --> 28:21.500
for our marriage license,
now, I filled in most of it

28:21.500 --> 28:25.000
but I wasn't exactly sure
what to put here.

28:25.000 --> 28:27.333
Do you plan
on changing your name?

28:27.333 --> 28:29.208
Oh, I hadn't thought about it.

28:29.208 --> 28:33.208
Well, I'm-I'm okay
with whatever you want to do.

28:33.208 --> 28:35.250
I'll keep it, then.

28:37.333 --> 28:39.542
Honey, what's wrong?

28:39.542 --> 28:43.041
- I'm nervous.
- It's perfectly natural.

28:43.041 --> 28:44.375
Alright, listen.

28:44.375 --> 28:47.875
All you have to do
is sign on the dotted line

28:47.875 --> 28:50.542
and, I promise you,
I will fill out all the rest.

28:50.542 --> 28:51.959
Yeah.

29:08.000 --> 29:09.166
[sighing]

29:09.166 --> 29:11.542
I'm sorry, uh, Derrick. I...

29:11.542 --> 29:13.417
It's okay. It's okay.

29:13.417 --> 29:15.917
Just take a breath.

29:15.917 --> 29:18.291
You know, I'm sure all brides
get nervous on the day--

29:18.291 --> 29:21.458
Well, I just thought that
I'd have more time to be sure.

29:21.458 --> 29:22.792
About what?

29:25.083 --> 29:26.500
About us.

29:30.583 --> 29:32.375
Oh.

29:34.625 --> 29:36.125
Okay.

29:37.458 --> 29:39.041
Okay.

29:42.125 --> 29:43.375
I see.

29:48.792 --> 29:50.834
Is it Red Raymond?

29:54.792 --> 29:56.708
I'm sorry.

29:58.959 --> 30:00.458
Oh, wow.

30:04.959 --> 30:07.834
Yeah, he warned me.

30:10.125 --> 30:11.458
Look, it's, it's my fault.

30:11.458 --> 30:13.000
Blame me. It's my fault.

30:13.000 --> 30:16.625
No. No, I'm not gonna blame you.

30:16.625 --> 30:19.166
And I'm not gonna blow up at you
and storm of here

30:19.166 --> 30:24.250
like some child. That's not
how I want this to end.

30:24.250 --> 30:28.166
All I ever wanted
was to make you happy.

30:28.166 --> 30:31.375
That's it, and I'm so sorry
that I couldn't do that.

30:33.125 --> 30:36.083
But I still love you, Vanessa...

30:37.458 --> 30:39.750
...and I always will.

30:40.875 --> 30:42.333
Alright.

30:42.333 --> 30:44.500
Just, uh...

30:44.500 --> 30:46.458
...tell Red
that I said congratulations.

30:48.708 --> 30:50.792
And I wish you two
the very best.

30:55.375 --> 30:58.333
[instrumental music]

31:01.834 --> 31:03.625
[sobbing]

31:09.291 --> 31:11.667
It was awful.

31:11.667 --> 31:13.000
I don't know
what I would've done

31:13.000 --> 31:15.208
if your mom hadn't stepped in.

31:17.333 --> 31:19.875
Is there something
wrong with me, Marti?

31:19.875 --> 31:23.625
The fact that I'd want
Dan back after what he...

31:24.750 --> 31:27.041
What you guys did?

31:28.792 --> 31:31.166
You're a wonderful person
with love and forgiveness

31:31.166 --> 31:33.000
in your heart.

31:33.000 --> 31:35.542
There is nothing wrong with you.

31:38.708 --> 31:41.000
You know, uh,
we got through the night

31:41.000 --> 31:43.708
without hurting our friendship.

31:43.708 --> 31:46.500
I wasn't totally
certain we would.

31:46.500 --> 31:47.708
Yeah.

31:47.708 --> 31:49.708
I'm proud of that.

31:49.708 --> 31:51.417
Proud of us.

31:52.333 --> 31:53.750
Me, too.

32:03.208 --> 32:04.625
[clears throat]

32:05.959 --> 32:07.750
Look, I...

32:07.750 --> 32:11.917
...know everything
has changed between us...

32:11.917 --> 32:14.542
...but I just can't stand by
and watch my former best friend

32:14.542 --> 32:17.083
and my new best friend
make a terrible mistake.

32:17.083 --> 32:20.250
Is that what you were
gonna say to me earlier?

32:21.875 --> 32:25.542
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

32:25.542 --> 32:29.917
Because what, what I wanted
to say to you was that...

32:29.917 --> 32:32.583
...you were right before...

32:32.583 --> 32:35.667
...about us being friends.

32:35.667 --> 32:37.500
It's what we're best at...

32:38.917 --> 32:41.417
...what we were meant to be.

32:44.291 --> 32:46.917
- You really mean that?
- Yeah.

32:48.333 --> 32:49.917
Yeah, I do.

32:52.250 --> 32:54.417
I've really missed you.

32:54.417 --> 32:55.959
I missed the heck out of you.

32:55.959 --> 32:57.417
[chuckling]

32:58.834 --> 33:01.250
Now, get your ass
over to Savannah.

33:01.250 --> 33:03.625
Man.

33:03.625 --> 33:05.875
What am I supposed to say?

33:05.875 --> 33:07.500
Dan.

33:09.750 --> 33:12.083
If you have to ask...

33:12.083 --> 33:14.041
...you don't deserve her.

33:20.792 --> 33:21.792
[alarm buzzing]

33:32.000 --> 33:33.458
Hey.

33:42.041 --> 33:44.834
It's good to see you.

33:44.834 --> 33:47.375
- Jake, I'm so sorry.
- Oh, no, that's okay.

33:47.375 --> 33:50.125
I mean...I know you're busy.

33:50.125 --> 33:53.500
No, I mean,
I'm sorry you're here.

33:54.166 --> 33:55.625
Oh.

33:55.625 --> 33:58.667
Yeah. Me, too.

33:58.667 --> 34:01.166
All that stuff I said was lies.

34:01.166 --> 34:02.959
Everything I said to you
at the football stadium

34:02.959 --> 34:07.542
about believing in God
and God having some bigger plan.

34:09.542 --> 34:11.208
I don't understand.

34:11.208 --> 34:15.000
I...I just said it all
so you would confess.

34:19.875 --> 34:22.708
I just wanted
to save the Hellcats.

34:22.708 --> 34:26.375
You're saying it's your fault
that I'm here?

34:27.792 --> 34:29.708
Yeah.

34:32.875 --> 34:35.041
Alice, I'm here
because I robbed the pharmacy

34:35.041 --> 34:37.125
and let an innocent man
take the blame.

34:37.125 --> 34:39.208
But you didn't have to confess.

34:39.208 --> 34:41.041
But I wasn't
getting away with it.

34:41.041 --> 34:43.583
All you did was make sure
that when I ended up behind bars

34:43.583 --> 34:47.417
I felt like a decent person.

34:47.417 --> 34:50.750
You see Marti,
tell her she was right.

34:50.750 --> 34:52.917
I am sleeping better.

34:52.917 --> 34:54.625
[chuckling]
I...

34:54.625 --> 34:57.208
I don't know what to say.

34:57.208 --> 34:59.417
That's a first.

34:59.417 --> 35:01.166
[both chuckling]

35:01.166 --> 35:04.750
Oh, you know,
I may have played this wrong.

35:04.750 --> 35:07.792
Maybe I should have let you
think this was your fault.

35:07.792 --> 35:09.417
Why?

35:09.417 --> 35:12.917
I could guilt you
into coming back to visit again.

35:12.917 --> 35:16.583
Uh, well, guilt has never been
a great motivator for me.

35:16.583 --> 35:18.667
It was this time.

35:21.583 --> 35:24.166
Maybe I could come back, anyway.

35:30.625 --> 35:33.917
You know, I could,
uh, make it worth your while.

35:33.917 --> 35:36.750
I hear
a lot of great jokes in here.

35:36.750 --> 35:38.959
- Really?
- No.

